reviews.text: Lots to do around the area, nice restaurants and cafes, a huge market!
People working on this station are useless, just standing there watching their facebooks, no help from them at all. Should be replaced

The guy who served me was friendly, but there was no salt on the chips, that was the first thing I noticed about the food.  The chicken burger in pitta bread, with mango and lime was uninspiring, but I was more focused on getting onto the Tube with my little daughter without spilling everything, so I might not have been able to enjoy the meal the way I wanted. I'm not a fan of this kind of food, really.

Large, multifunctional metro and overground stops. There is a large bus stop on the front which offers transport in all directions in the area. Well-equipped, functional and with high attendance.
I Recommended! 
5 stars
Old and over subscribed station which nevertheless offers good links for Liverpool Street and Victoria in the South and Chingford in the North
